Colour:
Integument mostly yellow. Apex of mandible black; clypeus with two oval pale-brown spots on upper disc; parocular area with a long yellow stripe along the eye margin; frons black with a yellow spot on disc (
Fig. 92
). Pedicel and F1–F2, reddish yellow; F3– F11, reddish brown. Mesoscutum black, with narrow yellow stripes on disc and lateral margins (
Fig. 109
). Terga with marginal zone reddish brown. Hind basitarsus light brown; tibial spurs yellow. Wing membrane yellow, infumated, with yellowish microtrichiae; apical portion darkened by brown microtrichiae; veins and pterostigma orange yellow.
